<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The OS_DEBUG macro is defined as empty (#define OS_DEBUG(__VA_ARGS__)). The statement OS_DEBUG("failed in clock_getres: %s\n", strerror(errno)); therefore expands to a null statement (no operation) and the strerror() call is not evaluated. Because the statement performs no action and its removal would not affect program behaviour, it is dead code and violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 2.2.
